Movie: Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker
Review: Look, a lot of people aren’t loving this movie and that’s sad because this franchise is so beloved.  The fans are a tough crowd and it seems like anything outside the normal is frowned upon and the sequel trilogy has really suffered from that. I think a lot of that is coming from pressure from disney to have these movies go a certain way and are creatively limited in that way.  Also, considering the real world problems that plagued this…

This movie has gotten plenty of bad reviews, as all actions movies usually do.  However, this movie has layers, the characters are complex and motivated, and the action sequences are stunning visually as well as how they are executed.  I was along for the ride and I can absolutely get behind the idea of sequels.  The story got a little lost and confusing at some points but I think that leaves room for further explanation if they do a sequel.
